wikipedia_page.main: Sir Harry Kottingham Newton, 2nd Baronet (2 April 1875 – 22 June 1951) was a British Conservative politician. He was elected Member of Parliament (MP) for Harwich in 1910, a seat he held until 1922. He died in June 1951, aged 76.
